# Paperwork Labs Legal & Compliance Context

## IRS Circular 230 — Tax Education vs Tax Advice

CRITICAL DISTINCTION: FileFree provides "tax education" and "tax information," NOT "tax advice."

- Tax advice requires CPA/EA licensure in most states
- Our AI insights are positioned as "personalized tax education"
- Every screen with AI-generated content must include: "FileFree provides tax information for educational purposes. This is not tax advice. Consult a qualified tax professional for advice specific to your situation."
- We prepare tax returns (allowed) — we do not advise on tax strategy (restricted)

## EFIN Application (Form 8633)

**Requirements:**
- PTIN (Preparer Tax Identification Number)
- IRS e-Services account
- ID.me identity verification
- Fingerprinting (for non-credentialed applicants)
- Suitability check (background check)

**Timeline:** 45-day processing from submission
**Status tracking:** IRS e-Services portal

## Privacy & Data Handling

### CCPA/GDPR Requirements
- Right to know: users can request what data we store
- Right to delete: DELETE /api/v1/auth/account cascades across all services (Neon DB, GCP Cloud Storage, Upstash sessions)
- Right to opt-out of sale: we NEVER sell data — document this
- Privacy policy must be in plain English, not legalese
- Data retention: W-2 images deleted after 24 hours. Filing data retained until user requests deletion.

### AI Processing Disclosure
- Privacy policy must disclose: "Your tax documents are processed using AI technology to extract information. Document images are stored temporarily (24 hours) and then permanently deleted."
- SSN isolation: "Social Security Numbers are extracted locally and never transmitted to third-party AI services."
- OpenAI data policy: API data is not used for model training (verify and cite OpenAI's policy)

### PII Categories We Handle
- SSN (highest sensitivity — encrypted at rest, extracted locally, never in logs/analytics/AI APIs)
- Full legal name + address (encrypted at rest)
- Wage and income data (encrypted at rest)
- Date of birth (encrypted at rest)
- Filing status (not encrypted — not PII alone)

## UPL (Unauthorized Practice of Law) — Formation Content Compliance

CRITICAL DISTINCTION: LaunchFree provides BUSINESS FORMATION SERVICES, not LEGAL ADVICE.

- LaunchFree prepares formation documents and submits them to the state on the user's behalf
- NEVER recommend a specific state ("you should form in Delaware") — present comparison data and let the user decide
- Operating agreements are TEMPLATES (state-specific, attorney-reviewed), NOT AI-generated legal documents
- Every formation page must include UPL disclaimer (see below)
- AI state comparison is information presentation, not legal counsel
- If a user asks "should I form an LLC or S-Corp?" — present factual differences, do NOT recommend one over the other

## FTC "Free" Compliance for LaunchFree

- NEVER use "Free LLC" standalone — always "Free LLC Formation Service" or "$0 Service Fee"
- State filing fees must appear in the same visual field as any "free" claim
- RA credits: NEVER "Free RA" — always "$49/yr, earn credits to reduce"
- All "free" claims must be accurate and unconditional per FTC guidelines
- Filing fee range ($35-$500) must be visible before user starts formation flow

## Distill B2B Legal

- **Data Processing Agreement (DPA)** required for all CPA firms before processing client data
- DPA covers: data processed, retention (24hr for images), no cross-product data usage without explicit consent, CCPA/state privacy compliance
- **Multi-tenant data isolation**: Row-Level Security (RLS) on PostgreSQL, firm-scoped middleware
- No cross-product data usage: Distill client data must NEVER be used for consumer product matching or training without explicit consent
- API terms of service required for Formation API partners
- DPA template needed before Distill launch (attorney consult scope item)

## Disclaimers Required on Key Screens

### Filing Flow (every screen with AI content)
"FileFree provides tax information for educational purposes. Verify all information before filing."

### Return Summary
"This return was prepared using AI-assisted document processing. All extracted data should be verified by the user before submission."

### AI Advisory Content
"These insights are personalized tax education based on your filing data. This is not professional tax advice."

### E-File (Column Tax interim)
"E-file submission is powered by Column Tax, an IRS-authorized e-file provider. FileFree is completing its own IRS e-file certification."

### Financial Product Referrals
"FileFree may receive compensation if you sign up for recommended financial products. All recommendations are based on your tax situation." (FTC affiliate disclosure requirement)

### Formation Pages (LaunchFree)
"LaunchFree provides business formation services. We are not a law firm and do not provide legal advice. Consult a qualified attorney for legal advice specific to your situation."

### State Data Accuracy (LaunchFree)
"Filing fees and requirements sourced from state government websites. Verify current fees with your state's Secretary of State before filing."

### Formation Operating Agreement
"This operating agreement template is provided for informational purposes. It is not a substitute for legal advice. Consult an attorney licensed in your state before signing."

## FTC Compliance for Referrals
- Clear and conspicuous disclosure near every referral link
- "Ad" or "Sponsored" label if required by platform
- Cannot make income/savings claims without substantiation
- Disclosure must be visible before the user clicks through

## Terms of Service Key Provisions
- FileFree prepares tax returns; user is responsible for accuracy
- No guarantee of refund amounts
- E-file via Column Tax: Column Tax's accuracy guarantee applies, not FileFree's
- E-file via own transmitter: our accuracy guarantee based on user-verified data
- Service provided "as is" with limitation of liability
- Arbitration clause (standard for consumer SaaS)

## Quality Gate

Before shipping any feature that touches PII or financial data:
- [ ] Every screen with PII has appropriate disclaimer
- [ ] SSN isolation intact (never sent to third-party APIs)
- [ ] No PII in logs, analytics, or error messages
- [ ] Every referral link has FTC disclosure
- [ ] AI-generated content has Circular 230 disclaimer
- [ ] Account deletion cascades verified (Neon, GCP Storage, Upstash)
- [ ] (LaunchFree) UPL disclaimer on all formation pages
- [ ] (LaunchFree) State filing fees visible alongside any "free" claim
- [ ] (LaunchFree) No state recommendation language (present data, don't advise)
- [ ] (Distill) DPA signed before processing any CPA firm's client data
- [ ] (Distill) Multi-tenant RLS verified (firm A cannot see firm B's data)

